<h3 id="note-the-crushers-hut-cannot-be-built-until-you-have-a-level-1-stonemasons-hut-and-have-finished-the-research-in-the-university">Note: The Crusherâ€™s Hut cannot be built until you have a level 1 <a href="../../source/buildings/stonemason">Stonemasonâ€™s Hut</a> and have finished the research in the <a href="../../source/buildings/university">University</a>.</h3>
<p><br /></p>

<p>The Crusherâ€™s Hut is where the Crusher will take items and crush them into other blocks. The defaults are:</p>

<table>
  <thead>
    <tr>
      <th>Starting Item</th>
      <th>Created Item</th>
      <th>Ratio</th>
    </tr>
  </thead>
  <tbody>
    <tr>
      <td>Cobblestone</td>
      <td>Gravel</td>
      <td>2:1</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td>Gravel</td>
      <td>Sand</td>
      <td>2:1</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td>Sand</td>
      <td>Clay</td>
      <td>2:1</td>
    </tr>
  </tbody>
</table>

<p>The higher the level of the Crusherâ€™s Hut, the more daily output the Crusher can handle. So:</p>

<table>
  <thead>
    <tr>
      <th>Building Level</th>
      <th>Daily Max</th>
    </tr>
  </thead>
  <tbody>
    <tr>
      <td>1</td>
      <td>16</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td>2</td>
      <td>64</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td>3</td>
      <td>144</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td>4</td>
      <td>256</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td>5</td>
      <td>999</td>
    </tr>
  </tbody>
</table>

